How to integrate with third-party JavaScript libraries

It is likely that you will want to run your JavaScript code only once the page has been fully loaded by the browser. Using the document$ observable exported by Material for MkDocs ensures your code runs after each page load with instant navigation enabled.

document$.subscribe(function () {
  console.log("Initialize third-party libraries here");
});

For full documentation visit mkdocs.org.

docs.title: Commands
docs.text:
• mkdocs new [dir-name] - Create a new project.
  • mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server.
  • mkdocs build - Build the documentation site.
  • mkdocs -h - Print help message and exit.

docs.title: Project layout
docs.text:
mkdocs.yml    # The configuration file.
docs/
    index.md  # The documentation homepage.
    ...       # Other markdown pages, images and other files.
